# svg2vd is the **SVG-to-Android-VectorDrawable
# converter** from Shopify — converts SVG files into
# Android XML VectorDrawable resources for use in
# Android apps.  Pivots from Java picocli (R276
# checkstyle) into the **Kotlin language tooling
# cluster**.  Sister to Android tooling (avocado /
# Android Studio's SVG-to-VD converter).  **MAJOR
# MILESTONE**: corpus's **first documented Kotlin CLI**
# AND first use of the **clikt** library — adds Kotlin
# to the cross-language CLI taxonomy (16 library
# variants now).
#
# Critical extraction note: svg2vd uses **Kotlin's
# `clikt`** library at `com.github.ajalt.clikt` —
# corpus's **first documented Kotlin CLI** AND first
# use of the **clikt ecosystem**.  clikt is **the**
# standard Kotlin CLI library — authored by AJ Alt
# (also author of Mordant terminal library + ColorMath).
# clikt is **Kotlin's spiritual equivalent of Python
# Click** (R266 uvicorn) — both are decorator/delegation-
# based DSLs for CLI declaration.  Extends the **cross-
# language CLI taxonomy** to SIXTEEN library variants
# (R276 added Java picocli; R277 adds Kotlin clikt):
# Rust (6: clap derive/builder/v3/hand-rolled/pico_args/
# lexopt), Go (4: cobra/pflag/flaggy/stdlib flag),
# Python (3: Click/argparse/Typer), Crystal OptionParser
# (R269), Haskell optparse-applicative (R270), OCaml
# Cmdliner (R271), C POSIX getopt (R272), Java picocli
# (R276), **Kotlin clikt** (R277 — NEW).
#
# Critical extraction note: svg2vd uses **Kotlin
# `by` property delegation** at Svg2Vd.kt:18-24 — the
# pattern `private val foo by option(...).flag(...)`
# uses Kotlin's **delegated properties** feature.  The
# `by` keyword tells Kotlin to use the right-hand-side
# (a `PropertyDelegateProvider`) as the property's
# getter implementation.  clikt's `option()` and
# `argument()` return delegate providers that wire up
# to clikt's parsing infrastructure.  Documents the
# **Kotlin `by` delegation CLI pattern** — corpus's
# first.  Distinct from picocli's annotations (R276)
# and from Python Click's decorators (R266).  clikt
# is the most idiomatic Kotlin CLI pattern because it
# uses Kotlin's first-class language features
# (delegation, type-safe builders, extension functions)
# rather than runtime reflection (like picocli) or
# decorator macros (like Click).
#
# Critical extraction note: svg2vd uses **chained
# DSL method-call type conversion** at Svg2Vd.kt:18-19
# — `argument(help = "SVG files").file(exists = true,
# folderOkay = false).multiple()` chains 3 calls:
#   1. `argument(help = "...")` — declare positional
#      arg
#   2. `.file(exists = true, folderOkay = false)` —
#      convert to `File` type with file-existence and
#      type validation
#   3. `.multiple()` — collect into `List<File>`
# Documents the **clikt method-chaining DSL** for type
# conversion + arity + validation.  Distinct from Java
# picocli's enum-based type detection (R276) and from
# Click's `type=click.Path(exists=True)` parameter
# (R266 uvicorn).  clikt's chained-method approach is
# Kotlin-idiomatic and lets each method specialize
# the previous one's type.  Each `.method()` returns
# a new delegate provider that wraps the previous
# one's behavior.  Corpus's **first documented chained
# DSL method-call type conversion**.
#
# Critical extraction note: svg2vd uses **`.flag
# (default = false)`** at Svg2Vd.kt:21-24 — clikt's
# `.flag()` modifier converts a regular option (which
# takes a value) into a boolean flag (no value; sets
# `true` when present).  The `default = false` is
# redundant (Boolean's default is false) but explicit
# for clarity.  Documents the **clikt option-to-flag
# conversion** — distinct from clap's `bool` field
# type (R260 dua auto-detects `bool` as flag) and from
# argparse's `action="store_true"` (R267 alembic).
# clikt requires the explicit `.flag()` modifier to
# turn an option into a boolean flag (vs the default
# of taking a value).
#
# Critical extraction note: svg2vd uses
# **`versionOption("0.1", help = "...")`** at
# Svg2Vd.kt:27 inside the `init { }` block — clikt's
# helper method that adds a `--version` option to the
# command.  The helper takes a version string AND an
# eager-callback (similar to Click's
# `is_eager=True`).  Documents the **clikt version-
# helper pattern** — distinct from picocli's
# `mixinStandardHelpOptions = true` (R276 checkstyle)
# and Click's `callback=print_version` (R266 uvicorn).
# clikt's pattern: call `versionOption(...)` once in
# `init` block; clikt auto-adds `--version` and
# handles the early-exit.  Plus clikt auto-adds
# `--help` (no extra config needed).  Corpus's **first
# documented `versionOption` clikt helper**.

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line

# 4 flag options + 2 positional arguments decoded
# source-direct from Svg2Vd at Svg2Vd.kt:18-24.
_arguments -s -S \
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help (clikt auto-adds)]' \
  '--version[display svg2vd version (clikt versionOption helper)]' \
  '(-f --force)'{-f,--force}'[force overwrites any existing files in OUTPUT directory]' \
  '(-v --verbose)'{-v,--verbose}'[verbose logging; show files as they are converted]' \
  '(-c --continue-on-error)'{-c,--continue-on-error}'[continue processing SVGs on error]' \
  '(-o --optimize)'{-o,--optimize}'[run Avocado on generated VectorDrawables (requires `avdo` on PATH)]' \
  '*:: := ->source_or_dest'

case "$state" in
  source_or_dest)
    # First N args are SVG source files (.svg, must
    # exist); LAST arg is the output VectorDrawable
    # directory (.multiple() on source means clikt
    # collects all but last).  Practical completion:
    # all positionals = .svg files OR directories.
    _alternative \
      'svg-files:SVG source file:_files -g "*.svg"' \
      'output-dir:VectorDrawable output directory:_files -/'
    ;;
esac
